Adventzeit

   Image associÃ©e


   Adventzeit


   There is nothing much I can do

   But I will do it with all my soul

   Hope is my middle name, so they say

   Faith stripped down slowly out of me

   But love remains as an ever blooming flower

   Let me put my hands close to the dancing fire

   For I need its warmth so much

   Infusing my body as a sweet little song


   There is nothing much I can do

   But I keep doing it since I can do nothing else

   Words fly from me as fragile butterflies

   Emptying my loneliness with distraction and smiles

   Filling in the silence of your absence with their moves and colours

   In the shadow of the streets, I whisper to the stranger inside of me

   Even though he would not reply but soothe my questioning

   Future comes closer like a morning after a long and noisy night


   There is nothing much I can do

   Never longing for dreams or gone memories,

   Because past and maybe have so few power

   Cannot quench my thirst nor satisfy my nosy appetite

   Keep the light on and walk along the cliffs

   I am this stubborn child willing to do the next steps

   Let's write it down like a recipe of happiness

   Patience has never been my favourite skill


   There is nothing much I can do

   But so much more with you


   18.12.18

   12h

   (Inédit)




