Goldfish

     RÃ©sultat de recherche d'images pour "poisson rouge "


   Goldfish



     Break the glass break the rules let it flow

   Let me dive into the big ocean

   Let me swim along the blue whales

   Enjoy the red sea and the green light

   I want to fight the sharks for once

   Sing and shout with manta rays

   And feel the tides on my spine

   And the cold currents from the depths

   Show me the rough world like it is


   Break the glass break the cycle let me breathe

   Freely into the large seas

   Straight forward across the waves

   Far from the sandy beaches

   Let me reach the horizon line

   Wait for the sunrise and welcome the sunset

   I want to dress myself with the seaweeds

   Dance around the gracious turtles

   And smile to the wide world


   Break the glass break the circle let it be

   Teach me how to plunge

   Show me how to fly

   Look at me in the eyes and give me a high five

   I want to feel the heat of the summer

   See the sparkling stars above me

   Ear the sound of the horn from these huge demons

   And give fishermen only rocks and plastic

   If only I could eat them alive


   I am this tiny goldfish

   Lonely and crazy in his aquarium

   Far from reality

   Lost in dreams

   Thursty for more

   Hungry for space

   Longing for noise

   Looking for troubles

   Spinning around with thoughts


   Watch out and

   Set me free.


   CF

   (Inédit)


